    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think the right way of handling this is that cell deletion should fire an\nevent that the raw_input widget can monitor and shut itself down if its own\ncell is deleted.\n\nOn Tue, Feb 4, 2014 at 1:52 PM, Paul Ivanov notifications@github.comwrote:\n\n> @minrk https://github.com/minrk and @takluyverhttps://github.com/takluyverand I were just having a discussion about this.\n> \n> our raw_input() that makes its way to the notebook respects\n> KeyboardInterrupt, but in debug mode, we're in a loop that just issues\n> another raw_input() prompt on interrupt.\n> \n> If you delete a cell that had a debug prompt, you currently _have_ to\n> restart the kernel in order to be able to do work again.\n> \n> One approach might be to have our pdb exit on keyboard interrupt when\n> running from the notebook. This would also help in cases where, even if the\n> cell isn't deleted, you still have to locate it and exit pdb in order to\n> continue doing work.\n> \n> ## \n> \n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHubhttps://github.com/ipython/ipython/issues/5026\n> .\n\n## \n\nBrian E. Granger\nCal Poly State University, San Luis Obispo\nbgranger@calpoly.edu and ellisonbg@gmail.com\n"
  },
